    </div>

    <p>The clinical evidence for oral collagen supplementation has reached a critical mass that most dermatologists now acknowledge. A 2019 meta-analysis published in the <em>Journal of Drugs in Dermatology</em> analyzed 11 randomized controlled trials with a combined 805 patients and concluded that hydrolyzed collagen supplementation for 4 to 24 weeks significantly increased skin elasticity, hydration, and reduced wrinkle depth compared to placebo. The proposed mechanism: collagen peptides absorbed through the gut travel to the dermis and stimulate fibroblasts to produce new collagen, elastin, and hyaluronic acid.</p>

