    <p>Goli RENEW NAD+ introduces a fundamentally different approach to anti-aging that targets the cellular machinery of aging itself. NAD+ (nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide) is a coenzyme found in every living cell that declines by approximately 50% between ages 40 and 60. This decline impairs mitochondrial function, DNA repair, and sirtuin activation — the three biological processes most directly linked to aging. Research from Harvard and MIT has identified NAD+ depletion as one of the hallmarks of aging, with studies demonstrating that restoring NAD+ levels can reverse age-related metabolic dysfunction in animal models. Nicotinamide Riboside (NR) is the most researched NAD+ precursor, with clinical studies demonstrating that oral NR supplementation effectively raises blood NAD+ levels by 40-60% within 2 weeks.</p>

