    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Anti-Aging Gummies</h2>

    <details class="fq"><summary>Do anti-aging gummies really reduce wrinkles?</summary><p>Yes, multiple clinical trials support collagen peptide supplementation for wrinkle reduction. A 2014 study showed 2.5g daily for 8 weeks reduced eye wrinkle volume by 20%. A 2019 meta-analysis of 11 RCTs confirmed significant improvements in skin elasticity, hydration, and wrinkle depth.</p></details>

    <details class="fq"><summary>What is the best anti-aging ingredient in gummy form?</summary><p>Hydrolyzed collagen peptides have the strongest evidence at 2.5-10g daily. Vitamin C is essential as a collagen synthesis cofactor. Hyaluronic acid supports moisture retention. Antioxidants like resveratrol and astaxanthin protect against oxidative damage.</p></details>

    <details class="fq"><summary>How long do anti-aging gummies take to work?</summary><p>Skin hydration improvements appear within 4-6 weeks. Measurable elasticity and wrinkle improvements require 8-12 weeks of consistent daily use. Hair and nail benefits take 3-6 months.</p></details>

    <details class="fq"><summary>Are collagen gummies as effective as collagen powder?</summary><p>Gummies typically provide 1-2.5g collagen versus 5-20g in powders. Clinical benefits were demonstrated at 2.5g daily, which some gummies achieve. For maximum anti-aging collagen benefits, powders offer higher dosing flexibility.</p></details>

    <details class="fq"><summary>Can you take anti-aging gummies with retinol skincare?</summary><p>Yes, they are complementary. Oral collagen works from inside (fibroblast stimulation) while retinol works from outside (cell turnover). No interactions between oral supplements and topical skincare actives are known.</p></details>

    <details class="fq"><summary>At what age should you start anti-aging supplements?</summary><p>Collagen production declines from age 25 at approximately 1-1.5% per year. Most dermatologists recommend starting in the late 20s to early 30s as prevention. Benefits can be achieved at any age, with older adults seeing proportionally greater improvements.</p></details>

